<h2>Common Mistakes When Testing APIs</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Forgetting Content-Type header.</strong> Many APIs return 400 or 415 if you send JSON without <code>Content-Type: application/json</code>.</li>
  <li><strong>Testing only the happy path.</strong> If your tests only check successful responses, your app will break on the first 400 or 500.</li>
  <li><strong>Hardcoding URLs and tokens.</strong> Use environment variables or config files. Test against staging, not production.</li>
  <li><strong>Ignoring response headers.</strong> Rate limit headers, pagination links, cache headers — they're part of the API contract.</li>
  <li><strong>Not checking response shape.</strong> A 200 with unexpected data is worse than a 500 — it fails silently downstream.</li>
</ul>

